<section class="section name-section" id="names">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">Name Strategy</div>
  <h2 class="section-h">Your Name vs. Alternatives</h2>
  <p class="section-sub">AMMAR is genuinely strong — here's why, plus two alternatives if you want options.</p>

  <div class="name-grid">

    <div class="name-card yours">
      <span class="nc-label">Your Name · Recommended</span>
      <div class="nc-name" style="color: var(--gold);">AMMAR</div>
      <div class="nc-arabic">عمّار</div>
      <div class="nc-meaning">
        Means <em>"builder, one who brings life to a place, long-lived, pious."</em> Rooted in the Quran (root ʿ-m-r) and carried by Ammar ibn Yasir — one of the most revered companions of the Prophet ﷺ. The name is personal, meaningful, and memorable in both Arabic and English markets. No known major clothing brand owns this trademark in Class 25 based on current searches.
      </div>
      <span class="nc-verdict verdict-yours">✓ Keep This Name</span>
    </div>

    <div class="name-card alt strong">
      <span class="nc-label">Alternative 01 · Very Strong</span>
      <div class="nc-name" style="color: #8896d8;">IMAARA</div>
      <div class="nc-arabic">عِمَارة</div>
      <div class="nc-meaning">
        From the same Arabic root as AMMAR — means <em>"architecture, construction, civilisation."</em> Feminine in sound, but carries gravitas. Works exceptionally well as a fashion brand name globally — distinct, searchable, and easy to pronounce. Likely clear in Class 25. Has a luxury fashion house feel similar to Maison or Atelier names.
      </div>
      <span class="nc-verdict verdict-strong">◆ Strong Alternative</span>
    </div>

    <div class="name-card alt">
      <span class="nc-label">Alternative 02 · Distinctive</span>
      <div class="nc-name" style="color: var(--cream-dim);">NASEEM</div>
      <div class="nc-arabic">نسيم</div>
      <div class="nc-meaning">
        Arabic for <em>"gentle breeze."</em> Beautiful phonetics, easy to say globally, and evokes lightness and elegance — perfect for breathable premium fabric. Less directly tied to Islamic history but universally understood across Muslim cultures. Searchable, brandable, and very clean as a wordmark.
      </div>
      <span class="nc-verdict verdict-good">○ Good Alternative</span>
    </div>

    <div class="name-card alt">
      <span class="nc-label">Alternative 03 · Heritage</span>
      <div class="nc-name" style="color: #c87850;">QALAM</div>
      <div class="nc-arabic">قلم</div>
      <div class="nc-meaning">
        Arabic for <em>"the pen"</em> — the first word revealed to the Prophet ﷺ. Highly symbolic and deeply rooted in Islamic culture. Strong brand story: a brand that writes its own chapter of Islamic fashion. Unusual in fashion, which makes it memorable. Risk: less intuitive connection to clothing for non-Muslims.
      </div>
      <span class="nc-verdict verdict-good">○ High Concept</span>
    </div>

  </div>

  <div class="trademark-note">
    <div class="tn-icon">⚠</div>
    <div class="tn-text">
      <strong>Important:</strong> This is not legal advice. Before launching, always run a formal search on the USPTO TESS database (tmsearch.uspto.gov) for Class 25 (clothing) specifically. Even if AMMAR isn't registered, check for phonetically similar names too. A trademark attorney can do this for ~$200–400 and is worth it before you invest in production. As a personal name used as a brand, AMMAR has a strong legal basis for registration.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

